Spring Boot : Spring Boot is a Java framework used to build web applications, REST APIs, and microservices quickly.

              Before Spring Boot, developers had to write lots of configuration code and XML files.
              Spring Boot makes development fast, easy, and production-ready.

---------------------------------------------------------
| Without Spring Boot        | With Spring Boot         |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| More configuration         | Less configuration       |
| Manual setup               | Auto setup               |
| Need external server setup | Embedded server included |
| More boilerplate code      | Faster coding            |
----------------------------------------------------------

1. Dependency Injection (DI) :  Spring creates objects automatically and injects them where needed.

    Instead of : EmployeeService service = new EmployeeService();
    Spring does it automatically using annotations.
            Example:
                    @Service
                    public class EmployeeService {
                    }
                        @RestController
                        public class EmployeeController {

                        @Autowired
                        private EmployeeService service;
                    }
Why important DI?
    - Loose coupling
    - Easy testing
    - Better code management



